    "is_free": true,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Wade still needs his MAMA.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras/3ded52c0d68537b0c0fdc77e894b6422.avif?t=1762257958\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras_big/3ded52c0d68537b0c0fdc77e894b6422.webp?t=1762257958 width=1560 height=463 /></span><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras/fb8765b0e19e3dba5b46a89afa9f09cf.avif?t=1762257958\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras_big/fb8765b0e19e3dba5b46a89afa9f09cf.webp?t=1762257958 width=1560 height=457 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Find your MOM by overcoming the obstacles, the narrator, and the traps that stand in your way.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The player moves forward, covered in objects scavenged from the streets — a wobbly basketball, a rusty barrel, even a burning box.  There’s only one goal: to find and reunite with the missing mother.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras/6422368f5c9d747556e609d3c9beb293.avif?t=1762257958\" data-big-src=https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3168490/extras_big/6422368f5c9d747556e609d3c9beb293.webp?t=1762257958 width=1560 height=462 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Find My Mom is the life story of a man who has lost his mother amid a powerless, stagnant life.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Does wearing a barrel on your head seem like a stupid idea? thank the developer.</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The narrator usually mocks you... but sometimes, he might actually help. Listen carefully to what he says.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The path forward is painful. A calm BGM might be the only thing soothing your heart.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Try rolling forward with a barrel over your head, or jumping high with a basketball instead. Whatever it takes—keep moving.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >There is a quit button. Just remember one thing: WADE still needs his mom.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>If the game feels too difficult, please contact your professor instead of the developer.</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This game is a student project — the difficulty is the result of the professor’s orders.</p>",
